    s_what: `<div class="rich-h1">What Is ADHD?</div>
<p class="rich-p">ADHD stands for attention deficit hyperactivity disorder. It is a condition that affects how your brain develops and functions — not your intelligence, effort, or character. It is one of the most common and well-studied brain conditions we have, affecting roughly 5% of children and around 3-4% of adults.</p>
<p class="rich-p">For a long time ADHD was thought of as something children grew out of. That is not accurate. Around 60% of people with childhood ADHD continue to have significant symptoms as adults, and many adults are only diagnosed later in life after years of struggling without knowing why.</p>
