    s_impact: `<div class="rich-h1">The Real-World Impact</div>
<p class="rich-p">This is not a mild inconvenience condition. The literature on functional outcomes in untreated ADHD is confronting.</p>
<div class="rich-h2">Driving</div>
<p class="rich-p">Untreated ADHD significantly increases crash risk. Newly licensed adolescent drivers with ADHD are 36-62% more likely to be involved in a crash in the first months of driving. Over the first four years of a licence, those with ADHD are 37% more likely to crash, twice as likely to drive while intoxicated, and 150% more likely to receive an alcohol, drug, or moving violation.<br><span class="rich-cite">Barkley RA et al. J Int Neuropsychol Soc. 1993.</span></p>
