<p class="rich-p">A landmark 2024 cohort study published in JAMA followed 148,578 people diagnosed with ADHD in Sweden. It found that initiating ADHD medication was associated with a 21% reduction in all-cause mortality and a 25% reduction in unnatural-cause mortality — deaths from accidents, overdoses, and suicide — over two years. A separate Canadian population study of 217,000 individuals found stimulant use was associated with a 39% reduction in all-cause mortality.<br><span class="rich-cite">Sun S et al. JAMA. 2024;331(10):855.</span></p>
